%% Mermaid architecture for 4-layer CI/CD
flowchart LR
  subgraph L1[Layer 1 — Commit Intelligence]
    A[Git Repo / Webhook] --> B[Commit Trigger]
    B --> C[Dependency Graph & Impact Analysis]
    C --> D[Selective Tasks: Lint, Unit Tests, SAST, Secret Scan]
    D --> E[Change Manifest (affected services)]
  end

  subgraph L2[Layer 2 — Artifact & Environment Build]
    E --> F[Incremental Build Orchestrator]
    F --> G[Hermetic Build (BuildKit/Nix)]
    G --> H[SBOM + Vulnerability Scan]
    H --> I[Sign & Push to OCI Registry]
  end

  subgraph L3[Layer 3 — Autonomous Validation]
    I --> J[Ephemeral Env Provisioner (K8s Namespaces)]
    J --> K[Integration / Contract / Perf / Chaos / Security Tests]
    K --> L[Validation Engine & SLO Evaluator]
  end

  subgraph L4[Layer 4 — Progressive Production Deployment]
    L --> M[Promotion Controller (GitOps PR)]
    M --> N[Progressive Rollout (Canary / Blue-Green / Argo Rollouts)]
    N --> O[Telemetry & Anomaly Detection]
    O --> P[Auto-Rollback or Promote]
  end

  style L1 fill:#f7f7ff,stroke:#333
  style L2 fill:#f0fff4,stroke:#333
  style L3 fill:#fff8e6,stroke:#333
  style L4 fill:#fff0f0,stroke:#333

  subgraph Infra[Platform Services]
    R[GitOps (ArgoCD/Flux)]
    S[Pipeline Engine (Tekton/Concourse)]
    T[Registry + SBOM Store]
    U[Signing KMS & Vault]
    V[Observability (Prometheus, OTel, Loki)]
    W[Policy (OPA/Gatekeeper)]
    R & S & T & U & V & W --- C
  end